  <h2>Wipro Limited: A Journey Through Time and Innovation</h2>
  
  <h3>Early Years and Foundation</h3>
  <p>Wipro, stylized as wipro, emerged onto the Indian corporate landscape on December 29, 1945, in Amalner, India, founded by Mohamed Premji. This marked the genesis of a company that would go on to reshape the global technology and business services landscape.
  </p>
  
  <h3>Transition to IT Dominance</h3>
  <h4>Shift to IT Landscape</h4>
  <p>During the 1970s and 1980s, Wipro transitioned its focus towards the burgeoning IT and computing industry in India. At this pivotal juncture, the company changed its name from Western India Vegetable Products Limited to Wipro Products Limited on June 7, 1977. This transformation culminated in the final name change to Wipro Limited in 1982.
  </p>
  
  <h4>Global Recognition and Milestones</h4>
  <p>In a significant stride towards global recognition, Wipro was listed on the New York Stock Exchange in 1999. Notably, in 2004, Wipro achieved a remarkable milestone by becoming the second Indian IT company to surpass US$1 billion in annual revenue.
  </p>
  
  <h2>Diversification and Demerger</h2>
  <h3>Strategic Demerger</h3>
  <p>In 2012, Wipro strategically demerged its non-IT entities, creating a separate company known as Wipro Enterprises. This move allowed Wipro to sharpen its focus on the ever-evolving IT landscape.
  </p>
  
  <h3>Notable Contributions</h3>
  <p>Before the demerger, Wipro's diverse business portfolio included consumer care, lighting, furniture, hydraulics, water treatment, and medical diagnostics, contributing approximately 10% to the company's total revenues.
  </p>
  
  <h2>Wipro's Global Presence and Recognition</h2>
  <p>In March 2023, Wipro marked a new chapter in its global presence by inaugurating its American international headquarters at Tower Center in East Brunswick, Middlesex County, New Jersey.
  </p>
  
  <h2>Wipro's Growth Trajectory: Strategic Acquisitions and Expansion</h2>
  <h3>Noteworthy Acquisitions</h3>
  <h4>California-based Tech Integration</h4>
  <p>In 2006, Wipro embarked on a strategic acquisition journey, acquiring California-based technology company cMango in an all-cash deal, reinforcing its foothold in the technology landscape.
  </p>
  
  <h4>Expanding Analytical Horizons</h4>
  <p>The year 2012 witnessed Wipro's acquisition of the Australian analytics company, Promax Applications Group, for A$35 million in an all-cash deal, enhancing its capabilities in analytics services.
  </p>
  
  <h4>Designing the Future</h4>
  <p>In 2015, Wipro expanded its global footprint by acquiring Denmark-based design consultancy Designit for €85 million, reinforcing its commitment to innovative design solutions.
  </p>
  
  <h4>Cloud Services Domination</h4>
  <p>Wipro's strategic move into cloud services consultancy materialized in 2016 with the acquisition of Appirio for a staggering $500 million, solidifying its position in cloud technology.
  </p>
  
  <h4>Strengthening Digital Customer Experience</h4>
  <p>February 2020 witnessed Wipro's acquisition of Rational Interaction, a Seattle-based digital customer experience consultancy, further amplifying its expertise in digital solutions.
  </p>
  
  <h4>Driving Financial Digital Transformation</h4>
  <p>March 2021 marked a significant milestone with Wipro's acquisition of Capco, a global technology and management consultancy specializing in driving digital transformation in the financial services industry.
  </p>
  
  <h4>Constant Pursuit of Excellence</h4>
  <p>Wipro continued its acquisition spree in 2022, signing a definitive agreement to acquire Systems Applications and Products (SAP) consulting company, Rizing Intermediate Holdings, headquartered in Stamford, Connecticut.
  </p>
  
  <h2>Wipro Limited: A Trusted Investment</h2>
  <h3>Listing and Shareholding</h3>
  Wipro's equity shares are actively traded and listed on both the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE), where it is a constituent of the BSE SENSEX index, and the National Stock Exchange of India (NSE), where it holds a position in the <a href="/nifty-50-companies-indian-economy-investment-potential">NIFTY 50</a>.
  
  <h3>Global Market Presence</h3>
  <p>Wipro's American Depositary Shares have been listed on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) since October 2000, affirming its position as a global player in the technology and business services sector.
